    <h1>Exercise - Tiered Direct Capitalization Valuation</h1>
    <h2>Build a NOI Statement to complete a Tiered Direct Capitalization valuation</h2>
    <p>
      Youâ€™ve been tasked with building a projected NOI Statement for the
      upcoming year for a 75,000 square foot office property.
    </p>
    <p>
      The current Market Base Rent for the property is $32 per square foot (psf)
      per year and the Operating Expenses are $9 psf per year, 100% of which are
      fixed.
    </p>
    <span class="inline-block text-lg font-medium py-2 text-gray-900">Space A - 30,000 sf</span>
    <ul class="flex flex-col gap-1 list-disc pl-12">
      <li class="text-gray-700 text-lg">
        Currently occupied by a multinational tenant with six years remaining
        on their long-term lease. The tenant is paying $28 psf per year in Base
        Rent and the lease allows for the landlord to recover their
        proportionate share of Operating Expenses.
      </li>
      <li class="text-gray-700 text-lg">
        The tenant also pays an additional $1,500 per month for parking and
        $500 per month for building signage.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <span class="inline-block text-lg font-medium py-2 text-gray-900">Space B - 45,000 sf</span>
    <ul class="flex flex-col gap-1 list-disc pl-12">
      <li class="text-gray-700 text-lg">
        Currently occupied by a higher risk tenant who has indicated they will
        not be renewing their lease which expires at the end of Month 6. The
        current tenant is paying $31 psf per year and the lease also allows for
        the landlord to recover a fixed $8.50 psf per year towards Operating
        Expenses.
      </li>
      <li class="text-gray-700 text-lg">
        It is expected that the Space will be released for a 5-year term at the
        beginning of Month 9 at a Base Rent of $32 psf per year and the
        replacement tenant will sign a lease that allows for the Landlord to
        recover $9.50 psf per year in Operating Expenses.
      </li>
      <li class="text-gray-700 text-lg">
        The landlord expects that they will need to provide the replacement
        tenant with 2 months of Free Base Rent as an inducement to sign the
        lease and the landlord also expects to have to pay a leasing commission
        of $30,000 to a broker.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The general vacancy reserve is 2% of Potential Gross Income and the
      general credit loss reserve is 1% of Potential Gross Income.
    </p>
