        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
    <hr class="mt-6 mb-6 border-gray-300">
    <h2>Task 1</h2>
    <p>
      Use the spreadsheet to build projected monthly NOI Statements for each of
      the spaces along with one for the total property. What is the NOI for each
      of the two spaces?
    </p>
    <div x-data="{showHint: false}" class="pb-4">
      <button type="button" @click="showHint = true" x-show="!showHint" class="button font-medium">
        Show hint
      </button>
      <div x-show="showHint" class="border border-green-500 rounded-md p-6">
        <span class="text-lg font-medium text-green-500 tracking-wide">Hint</span>
        <p>
          While the exercise uses rates per quarter, NOI is most often quoted as
          an annual basis, especially when being used to calculate property
          values. The total NOI across the four quarters is <b>$9,357</b>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr class="mt-2 mb-6 border-gray-300">
    <h2>Task 2</h2>
    <p>
      Using the NOI Statements you just built, determine the value of the
      property using the Tiered Capitalization Method (Forward 12-Months NOI)
      with a <b>6.0%</b> Capitalization Rate for Space A and a <b>7.5%</b>
      Capitalization Rate for Space B.
    </p>
    <p>
      What is the value of the property? What is the blended effective
      Capitalization Rate for the property?
    </p>
    <div x-data="{showHint: false}" class="pb-4">
      <button type="button" @click="showHint = true" x-show="!showHint" class="button font-medium">
        Show hint
      </button>
      <div x-show="showHint" class="border border-green-500 rounded-md p-6">
        <span class="text-lg font-medium text-green-500 tracking-wide">Hint</span>
        <p>
          Using the NOI Statement value using the Standard Direct Capitalization
          Method (Forward 12-Months NOI) can be calculated by dividing the NOI
          ($9,375) by the Capitalization Rate (7.0%) for a total value of
          <b>$133,664</b>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr class="mt-2 mb-6 border-gray-300">
    <h2>Task 3</h2>
    <p>
      If the landlord was aiming to sell the property sometime in the next few
      years, when would you recommend the landlord look at selling? Why at that
      time?
    </p>
    <hr class="mt-2 mb-6 border-gray-300">
